org.phlo.tuplez.operation
Interface GeneratesKey<KeyType extends Number>

Type Parameters:
KeyType - the generated key's type. Must be one of Short, Integer, Long BigInteger, BigDecimal
All Superinterfaces:
OperationOutput<Void>
public interface GeneratesKey<KeyType extends Number>
extends OperationOutput<Void>

Marks implementation of Operation as generating key values of type KeyType. Usually used on operations which represent INSERT statements.

This is required to execute such operations with Executor(opClass, input) or Executor(opClass), which return the generated key.

The column containing the generated key can be specified by annotating the concrete Operation instance with KeyColumn.

This interface defines no methods, it simply serves as a way of distinguishing at compile-time between Operations which return generate keys and such with don't.

See Also:
Executor(opClass, input), Executor(opClass)
